    <table style="float: right;">
      <tr>Directions;</tr>
      <tr><b>PING the network node to verify if it is active:</b></tr>
      <tr>1) Find and click on the <b>MONITOR</b> icon in the top left of the screen.  This will open a Command Prompt (blinking cursor '$').</tr>
      <tr rowspan="3">2) Type "$ping -c #" where '#' is number of pings, then the IP Address of the node you wish to verify.  <b>EXAMPLE: </b>$ping -c 7 10.51.10.80.</tr>
      <tr rowspan="3">3a) A successful test will show how many milliseconds it took to reach the device.</tr>
      <tr rowspan="2">3b) An unsuccessful test will result in "Destination Host Unreachable" with 100% packet loss.</tr>
      <tr rowspan="3">4) If test is unsuccessful, refer to the NET OPS Contact Sheet and call the RFComm Tech on duty (see schedule).</tr>
    </table>
    </div>
